        <updateDate>2017-11-14T20:04:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Public Housing Capital Repair Fund Act</b></p> <p>This bill reauthorizes the Public Housing Capital Fund Program under the United States Housing Act of 1937 through FY2020.</p> <p>The Department of Housing and Urban Development shall: (1) provide grants to public housing agencies (PHAs) for capital repairs that reduce health hazards in dwelling units, including mold hazards and lead-based paint hazards; and (2) make such grants to address the unmet capital needs of large, mid-size, and small PHAs.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
